                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d519">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9588: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-24T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 24, 1937—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>163. Your 297, August 23, 1 p.m. Nanking reports that the Embassy and other
                    Embassies are addressing a joint note to the Minister for Foreign Affairs and
                    that the Embassies in Tokyo are being requested to take similar action
                    there.</p>
                <p>You may inform your interested colleagues of the action already taken by you, and
                    if you feel that any useful purpose might be served thereby, you are authorized
                    in your discretion to participate with <pb facs="0469" n="462" xml:id="pg_462"/>
                    your colleagues in such action as may be decided upon regarding this matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
